  "link": "http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/07/intel-smart-bracelet/", 
  "description": "<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"chinese.engadget.com/2014/01/07/intel-smart-bracelet/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://o.aolcdn.com/hss/storage/adam/e36b25a53a8144bd14881f83447c9e92/intel-fashion-industry.jpg\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n毕竟穿戴式产品就像衣服（或称时装吧）那样，是要穿在身上的，所以即使功能强劲但外观不好看的话，也不一定会受欢迎。Intel 深明此道，在 <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/tag/CES2014/\">CES 2014</a> 上宣布将会跟 Barneys New York、Council of Fashion Designers of America 和 Opening Ceremony 三个时装业者合作，后三者将会基于 Intel 的技术来设计和开发出一款智能手镯。<br />\n<br />\n根据 Barneys 指出，这款手镯将会被「精雕细琢」，而且他们会将成为首批在自家店内售卖这款产品的零售商。此外，Intel 会跟 Council of Fashion Designers of America 联手为时装设计师和科技开发者建立一个社区，焦点当然也是穿戴式科技吧。不过计划的详情还是有待进一步的公布。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2014/01/06/intel-smart-bracelet/\">Engadget</a><br />\n引用来源：<a href=\"http://newsroom.intel.com/community/intel_newsroom/blog/2014/01/06/barneys-new-york-council-of-fashion-designers-of-america-intel-and-opening-ceremony-announce-wearable-tech-collaborations\">Intel</a></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/07/intel-smart-bracelet/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20802118/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/07/intel-smart-bracelet/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
  "title": "Intel 会跟时装界合作推出智能手镯"
